column28: Q7_Open Text Comment

column18: Is Degreed the best Saas Partner or Vendor you work with?
column19: What do we need to do to make us the best?
column20: Your feedback helps us improve your experience with Degreed! - Degreed has had a positive impact on our organization.
column21: Your feedback helps us improve your experience with Degreed! - I have a productive relationship with my Client Success Manager (CSM).
column22: Your feedback helps us improve your experience with Degreed! - My CSM has helped us make a positive impact within our organization.
column23: Your feedback helps us improve your experience with Degreed! - My CSM clearly understands what we're trying to accomplish in our business.
column24: Your feedback helps us improve your experience with Degreed! - My CSM effectively consults with me on how Degreed can help us achieve our business goals.
column25: Your feedback helps us improve your experience with Degreed! - My CSM equips me with the knowledge and resources to get the most out of Degreed.
column26: Your feedback helps us improve your experience with Degreed! - My CSM communicates effectively with our team.
column27: Q6_Support - How would you rate the quality of service received by our support team (support@degreed.com)?
column28: Thank you for sharing your feedback. Is there anything else you'd like to share with us regarding your experience with Degreed?
{"ImportId":"QID3_TEXT"}
In my Opinion The Partnership element of the relationship is deteriorating, our road maps seem to be further an further apart
I genuinely am so happy with the Degreed team. We were lucky to get to work with some fantastic people who have helped us drive forward a digital learning revolution at BAT!
You need to look at the enhancements and request list that customers are requesting, Catalog management is a nightmare process and needs to be addressed.
Some of our requests are taking way too long. e.g. Technical Success Manager has to check with Engineering and we wait........having to follow up. It's not efficient.
We are looking forward to use the TSM that is sitting in our timezone but we have started connecting with him/her

We need to partner on the best approach between support to daily operational needs with Degreed Support and Degreed strategic roadmap items. We are passionate to partner with you during early access phase of product enhancements and acknowledge we are partners in feedback during this phase. This seems to blur the lines between what should normally go to support vs. the TSM especially when features have a direct end user impact in production.  I am confident we will get there together.
Too many "formal" comms coming from too many sources.
Focus needed on core functionality before adding new features.  Fixing bugs and improving insights would make Degreed much more useful to us.

it would be helpful to get more technical information on releases. i.e. there are very strict privacy rules with in my company.  We need time to evaluate the new capabilities and decide what, if any, extra verifications are needed on our side prior to the release.

I believe the support we have gotten from our Technical Success Manager has improved from 2019 to 2020 but I do believe there is still room for improvement.  There still seems to be more of a focus on reacting versus stopping an issue from occurring.  It would be great to see a more proactive and predictive approach to support in 2021.

The issues already flagged to Kat and team regarding data/SAP HANA and China performance are becoming showstoppers and resolution progress needs to accelerate to enable us to deepen our commercial footprint further.

Both my TSM and CSM are nice people who want to do well, but I don't feel they understand our goals and concerns as well as they could. Separately, I think Degreed needs to do more to help clients secure valuable content, for example negotiating deals with providers and/or helping us get preferred rates. Without premium content, Degreed isn't very good.
We have had--and continue to have--an excellent relationship with our CRM and TSM. Expect it will continue as we continue on this journey together.

Both my CSM and TCM are great unfortunately I feel that sometimes they are not provided the details prior to a release to be able to quickly answer questions.  Sometimes finding these answer take a very long time.

I don't have issues with our TSM expertise - but I wonder if time management or just sheer volume of clients prevents him from taking action on a weekly basis. The other thing I am appreciative of is your onboarding style for new CRM/TSM to shadow and overlap and get to know clients  - I know that is more expensive on your end to provide that - but from your client end - it creates confidence that we are being taken care of and will be able to continue the evolution of our systems instead of backing up for context in order to get going again.

Reason for my ratings especially for the technical bits are based on while I understand neither Nielsen or Degreed had gone through a split prior, however they have deployed projects.  So there should have been more support/consult and proactive understanding of how our split would impact our set up of the added instance including moving users.  Much of the questions, issues and general understanding of how the product would react fell to Nielsen to figure out and work through.  It was frustrating given the feeling was that of not as in it to win it and urgency to help figure out impacts to ensure a good adoption by end users for day 1.  Much was trial and error on our part which took a lot more resource on our end to work through.  Given future deployment support is something that's part of the partnership ongoing, this was a bit disappointing and we learned a lot I think of where there may be gaps in product knowledge which we do need to work on for 2021.  Hoping ramp up of product knowledge will be key for moving the needle forward on both our engagement strategy as well as overall HR tech stack strategy.

Erika and Ben are amazing partners. As the CSM, Erika is extremely responsive to our needs. Her friendly, positive, can-do attitude is contagious, and her expertise is a huge asset for us as we learn how to best leverage Degreed at the Bank.

Andrea and Stefanie are an important part of our team's success in Degreed thus far. As we further clarify our goals and areas of focus through FY21 and beyond, we look forward to continuing to align with Degreed to cultivate a robust learning culture at Intuit!
Andrea is the best CSM I've ever worked with. Truly appreciate her time and efforts in making FICO successful. Thank you!
Special thanks to Kelly Youngblood and Lily Zaychik for helping us resolve difficult issues, and for always being so positive and supportive.

This year was rather crazy with our early reorg that eliminated the Macy’s colleague previously the POC for Degreed - followed by a 3-4 month furlough. So, it’s been slow ramping back up and “changing of the guards” of you will. At no fault of our Degreed partners, we haven’t engaged about strategy, business goals and aligning them to platform, and maximizing our usage of the platform. Although, Elaine has initiated multiple time and tried :) We are looking forward to engaging in a more meaningful, active way in 2021 — hopefully bringing these partners into my conversations / finalization of our internal roadmap and helping to drive our 2021 goals.

Daniel Burke has been amazing to work with and we consider him to be a member of the Travelers family.  Our success would not have been possible without Daniel, Stephanie Bottomly and others at Degreed!
Thank you very much for all you & Team does, greatly appreciative!

I have only interacted directly with Daniel. My experience is that his knowledge is amazing and his support through troubleshooting and questions is extremely responsive. He is a big part of our success here at Travelers!

Ref Q re achieving bus goals - this is not just from a CSM perspective but overall I would like to see much more reflecting back from Degreed team on how strategy, enhancements and new features will help Unilever to drive its own strategy, and really helping us to make those connections.  From a CSM perspective I sometimes feel Anthony is in a rock and a hard place and as such I want my feedback to be taken in this context.  How can he advise on enhancements and prep for our questions if the answers aren't there, or product enhancements are shared too early?  I appreciate Degreed work in an agile way, but sometimes all we need to do is scratch the surface to realise there is little concrete detail sitting behind items being shared. Again, this is not directed at Anthony. On the 'how' I think there is a development opportunity to think about the way in which he communicates with us - lengthy emails and links to KC articles would be more helpfully replaced with short live education sessions built into our regular calls.  He can sometimes come across a little defensive but this might be how he deals with some of the 'rock and hard place' stuff.  Overall he brings much more value and benefit than previous role incumbents.
We are a large company and we are filled with huge asks and challenges. Linda and Andrew definitely work hard to get the Degreed platform integrated  successfully

The survey discarded my initial response - frustrating. I had a great response about how much we adore our CSM and how Linda is a huge part of why we love Degreed. She's always actively working on our behalf. I have less experience with our TSM and that role has changed since we started our time with Degreed but Linda makes sure we have whatever resource we need to move forward regardless of who is in what role. I think it sounded better the first time but this still says what I mean - Linda is wonderful to work with!

We have had a great partnership with Degreed in the last two years. The CSM and TSM have been very supportive of our vision and demonstrated amazing support at all times. We are very excited about our partnership and look forward to this great team work in future too!
Very happy with the partnership we receive from the Degreed team. Linda Moeller in particular is a fantastic and responsive partner.

We just switched to a new TSM and so are eager to see if there is an improvement in our technical queries being addressed in a timely manner. One feedback I do have is re: agility of responses. I reached out to both Degreed and a competitor that we have a relationship with regarding information that our business needed to support an external client, and the competitor responded and took a call with the client team within 1 -2 days whereas it took Degreed > 2 weeks to route the call to the right person on the team.
Great support team and looking forward to the improvements related to APIs and reporting
Sara se ha involucrado y hecho que podamos ver más alternativas de cómo aprovechar degreed dando constantes recomendaciones

Our CSM is very enthusiastic and works hard to partner with us. We struggle internally with our transformation and matrixed org to ensure the right PEP resources are always engaged at the right level.
I'm excited for the items on the roadmap for 2021 and the direction Degreed is heading! Keep it up!

Daniel has been a huge part of the success of our Degreed launch and his continued support has helped us increase our overall engagement at State Farm too. He is also very responsive to answering any questions we have - and, not only gives us an answer but provides us with any additional insights or context to think about which is very helpful when we are problem solving or strategizing. I feel very lucky to have Daniel assigned as our CSM! It has also been so nice to have our TSM Kaley join us on our weekly calls. Having her there allows us to get quick answers and a direct line to support us through any of the releases or helping us trouble shoot problems or test new features and integrations. They make a great team and make our team better!
Yes - Overall Degreed is well received at AZ - However, Degreed need to continue to proactively invest in improving the product in China. It's a key market for us.
Degreed has set the bar for a true vendor partnership. Keep up the great work.
Although the access to a TSM is extremely relevant, I see him strugglin to provide us solutions on frequents glitchs
I'm very positive about the partnership we have with Degreed and the way our CSM and TSM think with us and go out of their way to connect us to experts at Degreed.

Our CSM is amazing and truly has a heart to help guide us in the right direction. Unfortunately often we are not finding the product offering to line up to what's been marketed. We struggle when we get into the weeds of the system to get quick resolution on glitches, brokens, and more. Often tickets are left outstanding or responses to tickets are not aligned to our expectations. Releases continue to vary and often dates are pushed back. It makes it difficult to plan new initaives around proposed system enhancements/updates. Elaine has done her best to support us in spite of the technical challenges.
Really appreciate the care and service provided by Daniel Burke and team.

Overall, we feel our CSM could be quicker to respond and often doesn't have any more information than what we're able to find on our own. We've wondered if this might have something to do with bandwidth for him - ie. he's responsible for multiple accounts.

I'd love our CSM and TSM to be more proactive in coming to us with new and innovative ways we can realize the value of Degreed for our organization. "Have you tried this, have you thought of this, etc" Also I'd like to see deeper information on product/tech capabilities, again more proactive vs. us having to come with issues.
We are very happy with our partnership with our CSM. he communicates regularly and is very thorough and detailed.
Our success team is awesome.  Even with changing people, they haven't missed a beat supporting us.
I LOVE working with Hali and Stacey! You guys are amazing! So thankful to have you guys supporting us!
TSMs are stretched very thin and CSMs should be briefed prior and deeper on releases. Sooner than the client.
Natasha has been a valuable player while I was helping create a more valuable learning experience in the organization

I think Kevin & Ben (CSM & TSM) are fantastic partners to my team. Our company is going through a lot of changes right now so we are still trying to figure out the best plan and they have been very supportive during this process and I'm grateful to have them as partners. Having worked with other learning platforms in the past, the customer service that Kevin & Ben provide is second to none. I couldn't be happier and look forward to where this year might take us.
Erika and Lily understand our strategy and are very responsive to our needs.  I appreciate the partnership and support we receive from the entire Degreed team.

El contacto y comunicación con el CSM y TSM ha sido muy efectivo, sin embargo la plataforma Degreed aún tiene muchas áreas de mejora, de parte de administrador principalmente en la generación de reportes, es necesario que podamos generar reportes en tiempo real y un tipo de reporte con toda la información desde el inicio, así como se maneja en los LMS. De lado del usuario final la aplicación mobile es otra área que debe de mejorarse pronto.
Our interaction with our Launch Manager-Divya was extra-ordinary ; she really helped us get geared up for launch and provided expert advice based on our strategy

I already completed this survey, but in case you did not receive it, I want to reiterate what I said in my previous response, Degreed is a great platform, but the people who support it, people like Carolyn, is what makes it excpetional. As an LXP, Degreed would not have been as successful if it wasn't for the effort made and energy put into the deployment, by people such as Carolyn Freeman, Krissie Billingham, Ian Wheelans and Andrew Eagan. Carolyn goes out of her way to ensure that my team and I are up to date with everything that happens in Degreed and all that Degreed does. She ensures I don't miss any webinars, forums, enhancements and knows exactly how to help me process all the information, activities and events, in a sensible manner, especially considering all the other work demands I have. She is always available. Her response time is nearly immediate. There is no obstacle she cannot move. She is great at interpreting our business needs and making suggestions on how we can use Degreed functionality or Degreed staff to assist. She is pro-active in her actions and her thinking and I love that about her...as I love thinking ahead. She is conceptual and strategic, yet pays attention to the operational detail as well. She is really an asset to the company, yours and ours.
Almost every time we send something to Support it is escalated to Tier 2, also when you have outages I should be notified quickly not me notifying you.

The direction of Degreed prioritizing Talent Management and Career Mobility over Learning and Development is concerning.  The 3rd party integrations and partnerships with Adepto and Visier are not the best choices.  The integration of the 8 point Lumina skill scale is very concerning as the cornerstone of your skill startegy.
Critical to be gamechangers in skills progression analytics, and integration with talent platforms like Eightfold
I'd love to be able to have an "admin" area to configure reporting to our needs, rather than using out of the box reports
It has been good! ZS would like more customization to list the organization branding when people login, etc.
A lot of enhancements can be brought into Degreed. Awaiting for reply from CSM for over a month on the few enhancement requests shared with them
I would to see the search functionality improved to make it easier to find things
Tem sido bem positiva, principalmente na relação com nosso CSM, que sempre nos apoia no planejamento de ações estratégicas, dicas, frentes de lançamento e construindo pontes.
Lo que daría un plus en la empresa es el SSO y que pudiera verse o ligarse desde nuestro portal institucional

Desire for additional flexibility/custom configurations and more system admin autonomy. Still surprised by the system limitations we encounter in comparison to other platforms. We appreciate the momentum of the releases/updates working to resolve some of this.

Quero sinalizar que a parceria do João e Edson tem nos ajudado demais. Eles são sempre muito presentes e trazem várias sugestões de melhorias. O João está sempre nos dando suporte na estratégia de engajamento dos colaboradores Embraer. Tenho certeza que com o apoio do João vamos alavancar a utilização da plataforma, pois as novas funcionalidades estão muito mais atrativas. Isso já trouxe um impacto super positivo para os líderes. João também sugeriu criar grupos entre líderes e liderados.... isso facilitou muito a conexão entre os times. O João fará algumas LIVES para falar sobre as principais funcionalidades  da Degreed para o relançamento da plataforma na Embraer. Estou muito satisfeita com a nossa interação e parceria. Obrigada!
Que nos apoyen con sesiones que sean de mayor valor para el cliente, por ejemplo como hacer el ROI de Degreed, mejores prácticas en LXP, etc.

Thanks for the opportunity to provide further details on my feedback. As we have shared with the Degreed team, we would benefit from: A thorough testing process to avoid turning functionalities off like we have done this year, Visibility on the Product Roadmap for some critical Degreed Functionalities for our strategy: Skill Review and Role Plans; and lastly, a more active response that translates into improvements in our partnership and the platform (e.g. we provided feedback on UX improvements on Skill Review and were told these would be reviewed for implementation. We chased a response for months, and in July were presented with a suggestion that includes only a pop-up message. This could have been implemented months ago, and we could have used it to re-engage learners with the Skill Review functionality).
Great client experience at all levels of support
Que se pueda obtener un certificado de Degreed y la empresa.
Que permiten realizar test o pruebas dentro de la plataforma

Considerando o atendimento técnico, percebemos diversas e grandes oportunidades na parceria. Desde a sugestão de melhorias para funcionalidades que impactam a UX, quando a flexibilidade técnica da empresa para atender (ou até mesmo personalizar) alguns cenários apontados. Nossa principal dor está nessa "falta de abertura" e, quando ela existe, o time técnico de engenharia ou DBA tende a demorar para solucionar os apontamentos.  Quanto ao atendimento de Sales, CEP e CSM, sempre foram solícitos e buscando apoiar nossas necessidades e iniciativas, assim como o time de suporte da Degreed que atua no Brasil (Joao, Renan, Gustavo, Caroline, por exemplo).
I'm dissatisfied with the new arrangement regarding technical support.  I much preferred the prior structure of having a dedicated technical partner at Degreed.

with the last question the only place where we're still wanting more is in the customization of onboarding, logo size and placement,  header, and possibly a footer. we've maxed out what exists, we'd like to be able to manipulate a bit more.

I didn't answer the previous question about ease of system integration because my company's HR / L&D team has not approved integrating Degreed with existing systems (Workday HRIS, LMS, etc).  Other functionality in Degreed - I wish reporting & analytics was more full-featured in the app.  Excel reports only have a couple tabs that I find informative (user summary and user logins).  I wish supervisors had more & better visibility, automatically, of their teams - regardless of the supervisor's permission level (they can still be a Member like everyone else, vs Manager or Learning Professional).
no

We love Degreed and our employees love Degreed.  We've had challenges with our Customer Support Rep.  While Anthony is personable and friendly, we don't feel that we get the appropriate level of support.  We have also had some challenges with the timeliness of support for issues and technical problems, although we have been addressing that with support area management.

I personally feel that while the functionality and customization features of Degreed are meeting our technical requirements, they have a lot of room for improvement. From a user perspective it works really well, but from an admin side it's still pretty clunky
I think Degreed is a great tool for having a structured learning path. I also find it very easy to use.

Entrei no final do projeto, além de ser muito bem recebido pelo time da degreed, eles ainda nos dão suporte e ideias para implementar e realmente obtermos o sucesso com a ferramenta. Desde já agradeço pelo apoio e parceria de todos!
Vuelvo a reforzar los niveles de servicio
O trabalho de você melhora o nosso.

Taylor has been a great partner in hearing our needs. We have maintained the Adoption workstream beyond launch, which has bubbled up many opportunities (or obstacles) that we share with him. He certainly listens and takes action on them, which is great partnership. There are always reporting features that can better help us tell our story, but we recognize that capability is evolving.
There are some basic features such as date range to extract reports that should be implemented ASAP
Should be proactive in managing success of Clients, which happened for us only after a year.

As admin it is hard to test or implement new features. Give us a sandbox feature to test and make new features integrations easy. right now for every new feature we need to create a test group which is not friendly.
Our client success manager has been phenomenal, Kelly Youngblood has been spending time with me and my team to better understand and utilize Degreed.

Very impressed with client engagement strategy and our ability to influence development of key features of the platform. Appreciate the product release webinars and high quality of events hosted by Degreed.

Sinto que a Degreed poderia começar a oferecer algumas funcionalidades de um LMS como, por exemplo, gestão de eventos, turmas, lançamento de presença, aceitando o formato SCORM de arquivos, oferecendo servidores para upload de arquivos, etc.. Também é necessário melhorar a qualidade de relatórios e indicadores da plataforma para que seja mais fácil extrair insumos sobre o desenvolvimento dos colaboradores.
Tiffany is excellent in supporting all things Degreed at JPL!
great product and we all love where it's going!

It seems there is a lot of manual/person effort to get to the end result you want to see for your users. FTP files have not worked at all successfully for me so far and have unfortunately added more time and effort.  Thankfully I have Carmel who is always ready to help guide, provide workarounds, and literally help me upload some information as we were running short on time, waiting for a resolution to the file load.  Thank you for your amazing support you provide Carmel!
note: it would be great to have a better visibility on the product enhancements we have submitted via our Sucess Manager.

Degreed has great technology but it requires some thought on how it positions itself to the teams that administer the talent development strategy and the managers that help grow individuals. At this stage the system is for the employee which is what we want but does not allow the rest of the organization to help guide or support those individuals. There is no functionality that helps support the strategic outcomes of the development teams. It is also concerning that to get this functionality it is at an extra cost. Reporting is not good at all which plays into admin teams not able to assist the population. This is not something that the CSM can solve and they can only do and manage the client with what they have.
Degreed has the flexibility of a platform that is needed at Nike, we need to do a better job of providing our user all the capabilities it offers to get the most ROI of the platform.

Our Customer support team has been great with an exception of around year 2 when we had a lot of change.  Ultimately we struggle with the constant changes to the system (UX and Reporting) that often break other things in the system or do not work properly.  I am also disappointed that the Skills Coach will become a "pay to play" feature.  We found that out AFTER agreeing to renew for 3 years.  While we are being grandfathered in, I anticipate there will be many technical challenges with this in the coming years and had I known, I would not have signed for 3 more years at all.
We are hoping to leverage Degreed with better adoption in days to come
There are a few basic challenges in Degreed that we believe should be easy to fix and we hope to see them on one of the releases soon.
Feedback
no
Degreed is Awesome!
I love Degreed!
Mayor flexibilidad u opciones para la entrega de reportes, solo nos daban una fecha y solicitar algo fuera de ésta, fue imposible
na

column19: provide all required features or adapt faster
column28: More focus on extended Enterprise and related functionalities, and address open issues which Degreed often rates as enhancement requests

column19: Continue to develop the software, especially the back-end and admin controls

column28: The reason for my one 'somewhat agree' is that we're really just getting started on our work together that is going to drive organization change and have a big impact.

column19: Model Bridge's chat function.  I can get instant in-app support, which converts to a ticket, and an email summary afterward.
column28: The CSM questions in this survey are irrelevant now that we have moved to a new model.

column19: Increase testing capabilities, provide governance reporting to support product maintenance, Rethink your skills position to drop Lumina scale, research partner relationships better (Visier, Lumina),  provide more flexibility in implementing releases

column28: No
Excelente do início do projeto até agora!
Elogio à Juliana Klayn e  Angélica Goldenberg pela expertise na plataforma, empatia, prontidão e pela visão estratégica de L&D que tem nos auxiliado grandemente!
Excelente primer experiencia hasta el momento!

column19: A larger investment in the core LXP product versus some of the new products that require additional costs.
More focus on the LXP and less on creating new products.

column28: hoje vemos a degreed como principal parceiro para nossas estratégias de desenvolvimento de lideres o trabalho consultivo nos ajuda identificar as oportunidade e escalonamento das nossas ações

column19: change your model to give us an extra resource in your tpc model
column28: sometimes your help or support people just give a standard answer that doesn't make sense

column19: You guys are pretty good, I just wouldn't say it's the best. We have a few others and I'd say NONE of them are the best; all have pros and cons.
column28: I am disappointed with the move away from better content management (capture and display of metadata information) towards fast-grab, information poor forms, content cards and processes. When we bought Degreed your content cards were information rich. Now they are glorified thumbnails.
My experience with Degreed has been great. All of our account reps have been kind, knowledgable and attentive. I look forward to continue the relationship.

column19: Support tickets can take awhile to resolve, some responses are not acceptable and problems/issues have been repeated.
column28: I think there has been a decline in response time and resolutions with the support team.

column19: Better roadmap clarity, improved process for getting traction on product enhancement requests submitted ie: getting them on the roadmap.  Issues are handled pretty well now with our Asana process etc.  But I feel like we never really got solid with the new portal on Degreed side for support, esp when it comes to the tie in between enhancement requests, roadmap and moving the needle along based on feedback provided.
column28: As reference for my feedback, I did not choose great on anything that did not blow my socks off.  Anthony and team have done a fine job, but I always look for opportunities to improve - so I don't put a "great" unless it's above and beyond my highest expectations :)

column19: Improve analytics and integrations so we can best leverage our skills and identify gaps.
column28: Carmel is an amazing CX.  We at CSG are sorry to see her go, but happy for her pursuing her DEI dreams!  Also, if Degreed could get their data and tech roadmap more agile it would make it the top LXP in the market.  However, flat file delivery and the  inability to quickly get at and promote the data story we want to tell is makes it difficult to keep the value of Degreed front and center for our Executive Leadership.
Degred is great!

lacking a designated CSM, big adjustment to new support model and confusion on what is and is not included with new model, feel like we are losing the pulse of Degreed and the direction of platform no longer clear
